WEBVTT

00:11:58.503 --> 00:12:02.433
But it's also because middle managers
are often reluctant to rock the boat.

00:12:03.100 --> 00:12:05.859
I talked with Stephen
about how to change that.

00:12:05.883 --> 00:12:09.091
(Conference) AG: ...because there's about
half a century of evidence

00:12:09.115 --> 00:12:11.667
on what you know is called
"middle-status conformity"

00:12:11.691 --> 00:12:12.851
coming out of sociology,

00:12:12.875 --> 00:12:16.276
showing that if you are at the top,
you have very little to lose

00:12:16.300 --> 00:12:19.685
by taking a risk, trying
something boldly creative.

00:12:19.709 --> 00:12:21.971
And if you're at the bottom
and you take a risk,

00:12:21.995 --> 00:12:23.882
you don't really have anywhere to fall.

00:12:23.906 --> 00:12:26.776
But poor middle managers
have spent five, 10, 20 years

00:12:26.800 --> 00:12:28.482
working their way to that position.

00:12:28.506 --> 00:12:30.664
And they have a lot to lose
by taking a risk,